l>\n        </description>\n</action>\n\n</actions>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nThe information below is give to help your work:\n1. The input_spec specifing the functionality of the RTL module;\n2. The generated testbench, which is verified correct by another LLM judge;\n3. The log generated by the simulation which is failed by the generated RTL and TB.\n<input_spec>\n\nI would like you to implement a module named TopModule with the following\ninterface. All input and output ports are one bit unless otherwise\nspecified.\n\n - input  clk\n - input  reset\n - input  in\n - output disc\n - output flag\n - output err\n\nSynchronous HDLC framing involves decoding a continuous bit stream of\ndata to look for bit patterns that indicate the beginning and end of\nframes (packets). Seeing exactly 6 consecutive 1s (i.e., 01111110) is a\n"flag" that indicate frame boundaries. To avoid the data stream from\naccidentally containing "flags", the sender inserts a zero after every 5\nconsecutive 1s which the receiver must detect and discard. We also need\nto signal an error if there are 7 or more consecutive 1s. Create a\nMoore-type finite state machine to recognize these three sequences:\n\n  (1) 0111110: Signal a bit needs to be discarded (disc).\n  (2) 01111110: Flag the beginning/end of a frame (flag).\n  (3) 01111111...: Error (7 or more 1s) (err).\n\nWhen the FSM is reset, it should be in a state that behaves as though the\nprevious input were 0. The reset signal is active high synchronous. The\noutput signals should be asserted for a complete cycle beginning on the\nclock cycle after the condition occurs. Assume all sequential\nlogic is triggered on the positive edge of the clock.\n\n\n</input_spec>\n<generated_tb>\n`timescale 1 ps/1 ps\n`define OK 12\n`define INCORRECT 13\n\nmodule stimulus_gen (\n\tinput clk,\n\toutput logic reset, in\n);\n\t\n\tinitial begin\n\t\treset <= 1;\n\t\tin <= 0;\n\t\t@(posedge clk);\n\t\trepeat(800) @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\n\t\t\treset <= !($random & 31);\n\t\t\tin <= |($random&7);\n\t\tend\n\t\t#1 $finish;\n\tend\n\t\nendmodule\n\nmodule tb();\n\ntypedef struct packed {\n\tint errors;\n\tint errortime;\n\tint errors_disc;\n\tint errortime_disc;\n\tint errors_flag;\n\tint errortime_flag;\n\tint errors_err;\n\tint errortime_err;\n\n\tint clocks;\n} stats;\n\nstats stats1;\n\n\nwire[511:0] wavedrom_title;\nwire wavedrom_enable;\nint wavedrom_hide_after_time;\n\nreg clk=0;\ninitial forever\n\t#5 clk = ~clk;\n\nlogic reset;\nlogic in;\nlogic disc_ref;\nlogic disc_dut;\nlogic flag_ref;\nlogic flag_dut;\nlogic err_ref;\nlogic err_dut;\n\ninitial begin \n\t$dumpfile("wave.vcd");\n\t$dumpvars(1, stim1.clk, tb_mismatch ,clk,reset,in,disc_ref,disc_dut,flag_ref,flag_dut,err_ref,err_dut );\nend\n\n\nwire tb_match;     // Verification\nwire tb_mismatch = ~tb_match;\n\nstimulus_gen stim1 (\n\t.clk,\n\t.* ,\n\t.reset,\n\t.in );\nRefModule good1 (\n\t.clk,\n\t.reset,\n\t.in,\n\t.disc(disc_ref),\n\t.flag(flag_ref),\n\t.err(err_ref) );\n\t\nTopModule top_module1 (\n\t.clk,\n\t.reset,\n\t.in,\n\t.disc(disc_dut),\n\t.flag(flag_dut),\n\t.err(err_dut) );\n\n\nbit strobe = 0;\ntask wait_for_end_of_timestep;\n\trepeat(5) begin\n\t\tstrobe <= !strobe;  // Try to delay until the very end of the time step.\n\t\t@(strobe);\n\tend\nendtask\t\n\nfinal begin\n\tif (stats1.errors_disc) $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", "disc", stats1.errors_disc, stats1.errortime_disc);\n\telse $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has no mismatches.", "disc");\n\tif (stats1.errors_flag) $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", "flag", stats1.errors_flag, stats1.errortime_flag);\n\telse $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has no mismatches.", "flag");\n\tif (stats1.errors_err) $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has %0d mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time %0d.", "err", stats1.errors_err, stats1.errortime_err);\n\telse $display("Hint: Output \'%s\' has no mismatches.", "err");\n\n\t$display("Hint: Total mismatched samples is %1d out of %1d samples\\n", stats1.errors, stats1.clocks);\n\t$display("Simulation finished at %0d ps", $time);\n\t$display("Mismatches: %1d in %1d samples", stats1.errors, stats1.clocks);\n\t\n\tif (stats1.errors == 0) begin\n\t\t$display("SIMULATION PASSED");\n\tend else begin\n\t\t$display("SIMULATION FAILED - %0d MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME %0d", stats1.errors, stats1.errortime);\n\tend\nend\n\n// Verification: XORs on the right makes any X in good_vector match anything, but X in dut_vector will only match X.\nassign tb_match = ( { disc_ref, flag_ref, err_ref } === ( { disc_ref, flag_ref, err_ref } ^ { disc_dut, flag_dut, err_dut } ^ { disc_ref, flag_ref, err_ref } ) );\n// Use explicit sensitivity list here. @(*) causes NetProc::nex_input() to be called when trying to compute\n// the sensitivity list of the @(strobe) process, which isn\'t implemented.\nalways @(posedge clk, negedge clk) begin\n\n\tstats1.clocks++;\n\tif (!tb_match) begin\n\t\tif (stats1.errors == 0) stats1.errortime = $time;\n\t\tstats1.errors++;\n\t\t\n\t\t// Display first mismatch details\n\t\tif (stats1.errors == 1) begin\n\t\t\t$display("FIRST MISMATCH DETECTED AT TIME %0d:", $time);\n\t\t\t$display("Input Signals: clk=%b reset=%b in=%b", clk, reset, in);\n\t\t\t$display("Expected Outputs: disc=%b flag=%b err=%b", disc_ref, flag_ref, err_ref);\n\t\t\t$display("Actual Outputs:   disc=%b flag=%b err=%b", disc_dut, flag_dut, err_dut);\n\t\tend\n\tend\n\tif (disc_ref !== ( disc_ref ^ disc_dut ^ disc_ref ))\n\tbegin \n\t\tif (stats1.errors_disc == 0) stats1.errortime_disc = $time;\n\t\tstats1.errors_disc = stats1.errors_disc+1\'b1; \n\tend\n\tif (flag_ref !== ( flag_ref ^ flag_dut ^ flag_ref ))\n\tbegin \n\t\tif (stats1.errors_flag == 0) stats1.errortime_flag = $time;\n\t\tstats1.errors_flag = stats1.errors_flag+1\'b1; \n\tend\n\tif (err_ref !== ( err_ref ^ err_dut ^ err_ref ))\n\tbegin \n\t\tif (stats1.errors_err == 0) stats1.errortime_err = $time;\n\t\tstats1.errors_err = stats1.errors_err+1\'b1; \n\tend\n\nend\n\n// add timeout after 100K cycles\ninitial begin\n\t#1000000\n\t$display("TIMEOUT");\n\t$finish();\nend\n\nendmodule\n</generated_tb>\n<sim_failed_log>\n{\n    "stdout": "VCD info: dumpfile wave.vcd opened for output.\\nFIRST MISMATCH DETECTED AT TIME 95:\\nInput Signals: clk=1 reset=1 in=0\\nExpected Outputs: disc=0 flag=0 err=1\\nActual Outputs:   disc=0 flag=1 err=0\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob140_fsm_hdlc/tb.sv:18: $finish called at 4006 (1ps)\\nHint: Output \'disc\' has 8 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 480.\\nHint: Output \'flag\' has 33 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 95.\\nHint: Output \'err\' has 25 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 95.\\nHint: Total mismatched samples is 41 out of 801 samples\\n\\nSimulation finished at 4006 ps\\nMismatches: 41 in 801 samples\\nSIMULATION FAILED - 41 MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME 95\\n",\n    "stderr": ""\n}\n</sim_failed_log>\n\n[Hints]:\nFor implementing kmap (Karnaugh map), you need to think and solve mismatches step by step.\nFind the inputs corresponding to mismatch in sim_failed_log, and set the output to correct value while maintaining other outputs.\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.ASSISTANT: 'assistant'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='{\n    "reasoning": "Looking at the simulation failure log, I can see that the first mismatch occurs at time 95 with inputs clk=1 reset=1 in=0. The expected outputs are disc=0 flag=0 err=1 but actual outputs are disc=0 flag=1 err=0. This suggests that the FSM is incorrectly asserting the flag signal instead of the err signal. Looking at the code, I need to fix the logic for detecting consecutive 1s and correctly handling the error case. The issue seems to be in how the transitions are handled after seeing 6 consecutive 1s. When we have 01111110, we should see flag=1, but when we have 01111111, we should see err=1. The problem is that the error case is not properly transitioning from S6 to S7, or the output logic for S7 is not correctly identifying the difference between 01111110 and 01111111 patterns. After careful analysis, I believe the issue is in the output assertions and state transitions.",\n    "action_input": {\n        "command": "replace_content_by_matching",\n        "args": {\n            "old_content": "module TopModule (\\n    input clk,\\n    input reset,\\n    input in,\\n    output reg disc,\\n    output reg flag,\\n    output reg err\\n);\\n\\n    // Define states\\n    localparam ST_IDLE   = 3\'d0;\\n    localparam ST_S1     = 3\'d1;\\n    localparam ST_S2     = 3\'d2;\\n    localparam ST_S3     = 3\'d3;\\n    localparam ST_S4     = 3\'d4;\\n    localparam ST_S5     = 3\'d5;\\n    localparam ST_S6     = 3\'d6;\\n    localparam ST_S7     = 3\'d7;\\n\\n    // State register\\n    logic [2:0] state;\\n    logic [2:0] next_state;\\n\\n    // Initialize signals\\n    initial begin\\n        disc = 1\'b0;\\n        flag = 1\'b0;\\n        err = 1\'b0;\\n    end\\n\\n    // Sequential logic for state transition\\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\\n        if (reset)\\n            state <= ST_IDLE;\\n        else\\n            state <= next_state;\\n    end\\n\\n    // Combinational logic for next state and outputs\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        // Default assignments\\n        next_state = state;\\n        disc = 1\'b0;\\n        flag = 1\'b0;\\n        err = 1\'b0;\\n\\n        case (state)\\n            ST_IDLE: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S1;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S1: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S2;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S2: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S3;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S3: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S4;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S4: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S5;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S5: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    next_state = ST_S6;\\n                end else begin\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S6: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    next_state = ST_S7;\\n                end else begin\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S7: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    // 7 or more consecutive 1s - error\\n                    err = 1\'b1;\\n                    next_state = ST_S7;\\n                end else begin\\n                    // Found 0 after 6 1s -> flag\\n                    flag = 1\'b1;\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            default: next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n        endcase\\n    end\\n\\nendmodule",\n            "new_content": "module TopModule (\\n    input clk,\\n    input reset,\\n    input in,\\n    output reg disc,\\n    output reg flag,\\n    output reg err\\n);\\n\\n    // Define states\\n    localparam ST_IDLE   = 3\'d0;\\n    localparam ST_S1     = 3\'d1;\\n    localparam ST_S2     = 3\'d2;\\n    localparam ST_S3     = 3\'d3;\\n    localparam ST_S4     = 3\'d4;\\n    localparam ST_S5     = 3\'d5;\\n    localparam ST_S6     = 3\'d6;\\n    localparam ST_S7     = 3\'d7;\\n\\n    // State register\\n    logic [2:0] state;\\n    logic [2:0] next_state;\\n\\n    // Sequential logic for state transition\\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\\n        if (reset)\\n            state <= ST_IDLE;\\n        else\\n            state <= next_state;\\n    end\\n\\n    // Combinational logic for next state and outputs\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        // Default assignments\\n        next_state = state;\\n        disc = 1\'b0;\\n        flag = 1\'b0;\\n        err = 1\'b0;\\n\\n        case (state)\\n            ST_IDLE: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S1;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S1: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S2;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S2: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S3;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S3: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S4;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S4: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S5;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S5: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    next_state = ST_S6;\\n                end else begin\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S6: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    next_state = ST_S7;\\n                end else begin\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S7: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    // 7 or more consecutive 1s - error\\n                    err = 1\'b1;\\n                    next_state = ST_S7;\\n                end else begin\\n                    // Found 0 after 6 1s -> flag\\n                    flag = 1\'b1;\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            default: next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n        endcase\\n    end\\n\\nendmodule"\n        }\n    }\n}')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.USER: 'user'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='\nOutput after running given action:\n<action_output>\n{\n    "is_action_executed": true,\n    "is_syntax_pass": true,\n    "is_sim_pass": false,\n    "error_msg": "{\\n    \\"stdout\\": \\"VCD info: dumpfile wave.vcd opened for output.\\\\nFIRST MISMATCH DETECTED AT TIME 95:\\\\nInput Signals: clk=1 reset=1 in=0\\\\nExpected Outputs: disc=0 flag=0 err=1\\\\nActual Outputs:   disc=0 flag=1 err=0\\\\n./output_t22c_qwen3coder30b_shard4_0/VERILOG_EVAL_V2_Prob140_fsm_hdlc/tb.sv:18: $finish called at 4006 (1ps)\\\\nHint: Output \'disc\' has 8 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 480.\\\\nHint: Output \'flag\' has 33 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 95.\\\\nHint: Output \'err\' has 25 mismatches. First mismatch occurred at time 95.\\\\nHint: Total mismatched samples is 41 out of 801 samples\\\\n\\\\nSimulation finished at 4006 ps\\\\nMismatches: 41 in 801 samples\\\\nSIMULATION FAILED - 41 MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME 95\\\\n\\",\\n    \\"stderr\\": \\"\\"\\n}",\n    "sim_mismatch_cnt": 41\n}\n</action_output>\n')]), ChatMessage(role=<MessageRole.ASSISTANT: 'assistant'>, additional_kwargs={}, blocks=[TextBlock(block_type='text', text='{\n    "reasoning": "The simulation failed at time 95 with inputs clk=1 reset=1 in=0. Expected outputs are disc=0 flag=0 err=1 but actual outputs are disc=0 flag=1 err=0. This means the err output should be asserted (err=1) but flag is being asserted instead (flag=1). From the specification, \'01111110\' indicates a flag while \'01111111...\' indicates an error. The logic looks correct in the S6 state - if the next input is 1 it goes to S7 and sets err=1, if it\'s 0 it sets flag=1 and resets. However, this doesn\'t seem to be working as expected because at time 95, the state is likely S7 and the input is 0, so it should set flag=1 and reset to IDLE. Let me trace this more carefully:\\n\\nAt time 95: \\n- clk=1, reset=1, in=0\\n- Since reset is high, state should be ST_IDLE (at least on the next cycle)\\n\\nBut the behavior indicates that at some point the FSM was in S7, then received in=0 and should\'ve triggered flag assertion. But it seems like in the actual simulation, it\'s going into an incorrect path. Let me focus more on how we determine the pattern 0111110 and 01111110. The key insight is that we\'re looking for 6 consecutive 1s followed by either a 0 (flag) or 1 (error), and we want to distinguish what happens in state S6 vs S7.\\n\\nI suspect that the issue might be in how the input in gets interpreted when we\'re in S6 (the state that represents having seen 5 1s) and then seeing a 1 (making it 6 1s) - in this case it should go to S7, but when we see a 0 it should trigger a flag.\\n\\nThe logic already seems correct according to the spec. I think I need to adjust the approach to ensure that when in S6, if we see another 1 (7th consecutive 1), we transition to S7 and set err=1; if we see 0, we transition to IDLE and set flag=1. But I need to make sure that these outputs are not being held back by combinational logic issues or timing issues.\\n\\nHowever, let me re-read the problem description carefully. The issue may be more subtle. Let me make a more conservative fix: ensuring proper state transitions and output assertions in all cases including initialization. The error may be related to how we handle the transition from S6 to S7, or when we get to S7 and have to decide to output err or flag correctly.",\n    "action_input": {\n        "command": "replace_content_by_matching",\n        "args": {\n            "old_content": "module TopModule (\\n    input clk,\\n    input reset,\\n    input in,\\n    output reg disc,\\n    output reg flag,\\n    output reg err\\n);\\n\\n    // Define states\\n    localparam ST_IDLE   = 3\'d0;\\n    localparam ST_S1     = 3\'d1;\\n    localparam ST_S2     = 3\'d2;\\n    localparam ST_S3     = 3\'d3;\\n    localparam ST_S4     = 3\'d4;\\n    localparam ST_S5     = 3\'d5;\\n    localparam ST_S6     = 3\'d6;\\n    localparam ST_S7     = 3\'d7;\\n\\n    // State register\\n    logic [2:0] state;\\n    logic [2:0] next_state;\\n\\n    // Sequential logic for state transition\\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\\n        if (reset)\\n            state <= ST_IDLE;\\n        else\\n            state <= next_state;\\n    end\\n\\n    // Combinational logic for next state and outputs\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        // Default assignments\\n        next_state = state;\\n        disc = 1\'b0;\\n        flag = 1\'b0;\\n        err = 1\'b0;\\n\\n        case (state)\\n            ST_IDLE: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S1;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S1: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S2;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S2: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S3;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S3: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S4;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S4: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S5;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S5: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    next_state = ST_S6;\\n                end else begin\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S6: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    next_state = ST_S7;\\n                end else begin\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S7: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    // 7 or more consecutive 1s - error\\n                    err = 1\'b1;\\n                    next_state = ST_S7;\\n                end else begin\\n                    // Found 0 after 6 1s -> flag\\n                    flag = 1\'b1;\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            default: next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n        endcase\\n    end\\n\\nendmodule",\n            "new_content": "module TopModule (\\n    input clk,\\n    input reset,\\n    input in,\\n    output reg disc,\\n    output reg flag,\\n    output reg err\\n);\\n\\n    // Define states\\n    localparam ST_IDLE   = 3\'d0;\\n    localparam ST_S1     = 3\'d1;\\n    localparam ST_S2     = 3\'d2;\\n    localparam ST_S3     = 3\'d3;\\n    localparam ST_S4     = 3\'d4;\\n    localparam ST_S5     = 3\'d5;\\n    localparam ST_S6     = 3\'d6;\\n    localparam ST_S7     = 3\'d7;\\n\\n    // State register\\n    logic [2:0] state;\\n    logic [2:0] next_state;\\n\\n    // Sequential logic for state transition\\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\\n        if (reset)\\n            state <= ST_IDLE;\\n        else\\n            state <= next_state;\\n    end\\n\\n    // Combinational logic for next state and outputs\\n    always @(*) begin\\n        // Default assignments\\n        next_state = state;\\n        disc = 1\'b0;\\n        flag = 1\'b0;\\n        err = 1\'b0;\\n\\n        case (state)\\n            ST_IDLE: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S1;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S1: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S2;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S2: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S3;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S3: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S4;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S4: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1)\\n                    next_state = ST_S5;\\n                else\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S5: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    next_state = ST_S6;\\n                end else begin\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S6: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    next_state = ST_S7;\\n                end else begin\\n                    // Found 0 after 6 1s -> flag\\n                    flag = 1\'b1;\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n            end\\n\\n            ST_S7: begin\\n                if (in == 1\'b1) begin\\n                    // 7 or more consecutive 1s - error\\n                    err = 1\'b1;\\n                    next_state = ST_S7;\\n                end else begin\\n                    // Should never happen in this state due to previous logic\\n                    next_state = ST_IDLE;\\n                end\\n         